<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
	<id>22412</id>
	<title>Set Environment Variable to always read from executing shell</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">I have a use case where I am creating an image that requires a number of environment variables for operation.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.2">It is an image that is to be shared among many users.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.3">To execute correctly the command line becomes unwieldy with the number of environment variables to pass in.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">If I could specify a number of environment variables in the Dockerfile like:</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="3">
			<sentence id="3.1">ENV OS_AUTH_URL
ENV OS_CLOUD_NAME
ENV OS_PASSWORD
ENV OS_TENANT_ID
ENV OS_TENANT_NAME
ENV OS_USERNAME</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="4">
			<sentence id="4.1">And then have any execution of that image automatically set those environment variables from the current shell variables (if set), it would make the execution much more user-friendly.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
	</description>
</bug>
